### Description

Effect don't run if there is an asynchronous or conditional statement.

```ts
 constructor() {
    effect(() => {
      if (this.insideSimpleEffect === 5) {
        this.insideCondition = this.count();
      }
    });
    effect(() => {
      requestAnimationFrame(() => {
        this.insideRequestAnimationFrame = this.count();
      });
    });
    effect(() => {
      setTimeout(() => {
        this.insideSetTimeout = this.count();
      }, 100);
    });
  }
```

However, it will run if you simply add console.log etc:

```ts
 constructor() {
    effect(() => {
      console.log(this.count());
      if (this.insideSimpleEffect === 5) {
        this.insideCondition = this.count();
      }
    });
}
```

Expect to run in such cases. Thanks.

